org.openehealth.ipf.commons.ihe.core.atna.custom

Class CustomXdsAuditor

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openhealthtools.ihe.atna.auditor.IHEAuditor
      • org.openhealthtools.ihe.atna.auditor.XDSAuditor
        • org.openehealth.ipf.commons.ihe.core.atna.custom.CustomXdsAuditor

  • public class CustomXdsAuditor
extends org.openhealthtools.ihe.atna.auditor.XDSAuditor
    Implementation of ATNA Auditors for the following XDS-based transactions:
    • ITI-51 -- XDS.b Multi-Patient Stored Query
    • ITI-57 -- XDS.b Update Document Set
    • ITI-61 -- XDS.b Register On-Demand Document Entry
    • ITI-62 -- XDS.b Delete Document Set
    • ITI-63 -- XCF Cross-Community Fetch
    • RAD-69 -- XDS-I.b Retrieve Imaging Document Set
    • RAD-75 -- XCA-I Cross-Gateway Retrieve Imaging Document Set
    Author:
    Dmytro Rud

      • auditIti51

        public void auditIti51(boolean serverSide,
                       org.openhealthtools.ihe.atna.auditor.codes.rfc3881.RFC3881EventCodes.RFC3881EventOutcomeCodes eventOutcome,
                       String userId,
                       String userName,
                       String serviceEndpointUri,
                       String clientIpAddress,
                       String queryUuid,
                       String requestPayload,
                       String homeCommunityId,
                       String patientId,
                       List<org.openhealthtools.ihe.atna.auditor.models.rfc3881.CodedValueType> purposesOfUse)
        Audits an ITI-51 Multi-Patient Query event.
        Parameters:
        serverSide - true for the Document Registry actor, false for the Document Consumer actor.
        eventOutcome - event outcome code.
        userId - user ID (contents of the WS-Addressing <ReplyTo> header).
        userName - user name on the Document Consumer side (for XUA).
        serviceEndpointUri - network endpoint URI of the Document Registry actor.
        clientIpAddress - IP address of the Document Consumer actor.
        queryUuid - UUID of the XDS query.
        requestPayload - the whole XDS request as an XML String.
        homeCommunityId - home community ID (optional).
        patientId - patient ID as an HL7 v2 CX string.
        purposesOfUse - <PurposeOfUse> attributes from XUA SAML assertion.
